name: RealCartoon-Realistic
description:
Want to buy me coffee? (Buy Coffee)

Please click "read more" to see more detail on the "why" for each version of this model.

**6/30/23: Added the Pruned Version of 2.0

...Please Share your images...Love seeing the results...

VAE is Baked in. ALL THE SAMPLES WERE RUN WITHOUT A VAE. MOST ON FULL VERSIONS.

The normal settings I ran it at are as follows:

  • Width: 512 (Have done up to 568)

  • Height: 768 (Have done up to 900)

  • Sampling Method: DPM++ SDE Karras/Eulaer A are the ones I use the most (Also DPM++ 2M Karras)

  • Sampling steps: 27-30 normally (27 is a nice spot for Euler A)

  • Hires.fix settings: Upscaler (R-ESRGAN 4x+ and 4k-UltraSharp), Hires Steps (10), Denoising Str (0.34 - 0.45 normally), Upscale (2)

  • Clip Skip: 2

  • Ran ADetailer to help enhance the eyes but mainly if I was doing a DPM sampler

Why another model?

This version of RealCartoon3D will focus more in the Realistic direction. Gives me yet another path to work towards. There is also RealCartoon-Anime to bring more of an anime look to the base model. I am hoping the RealCartoon3D version will keep that happy medium.

Why Realistic?

I want to have a Realistic Model that can do what RealCartoon3D can do, but more "real" looking. :)

About Version 1

RealCartoon3D is the base, but think I have found a good mix to add more realism.

About Version 2

This one took a bit. I think I have it where the realism is better, but the fun elements normally found in anime and cartoons still show up. Handles LoRAs well just like V1 but this one just comes across more real. Anyway, I hope you enjoy it. Please rate the versions!!
